    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>When the right-hand persistent cart sidebar is expanded, it behaves as a rigid, floating overlay that covers the right side of the main container grid rather than adapting the page layout, rendering elements underneath unclickable.</p>

<h3><a name="StepstoReproduce%3A"></a><b>Steps to Reproduce:</b></h3>

<ol>
	<li>Execute a search query (e.g., "toys") to pull up the product search results layout.</li>
	<li>Click the cart icon to expand the right-hand cart subtotal sidebar.</li>
	<li>Scroll down the main search results page to view additional products and the page footer.</li>
</ol>


<h3><a name="ExpectedResult%3A"></a><b>Expected Result:</b></h3>

<p>The main product grid container should dynamically scale or adapt from a 4-column to a 3-column layout when the sidebar is toggled open, preventing content overlapping and keeping all search results fully visible.</p>

<h3><a name="ActualResult%3A"></a><b>Actual Result:</b></h3>

<p>The expanded cart sidebar acts as a fixed layer that cuts off and hides the rightmost column of the product search grid, blocking core visibility and preventing interaction with structural components or page pagination underneath it.</p>

<p><b>Environment:</b> Production (Desktop - Chrome Browser)</p>

<p><b>Severity:</b> Low</p>

<p><b>Priority:</b> Medium</p>

<p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="https://harekarsakshi.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/attachment/content/10034" alt="Screenshot 2026-06-11 132140.png" width="594" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></p>
            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
